Package modelCheckCTL.controller.types.misc

Class Arguments

java.lang.Object
modelCheckCTL.controller.types.misc.Arguments
public class Arguments
extends java.lang.Object
Data type for storing the command line arguments for the Kripke filename, the optional state to check, the model input source (file/argument) and either the model filename or the model, depending on the model input source specified. This class does basic error checking for null values and text file names which don't end in ".txt". This class does not check if the model is well formed and does not read the specified files to get the kripke or the model.

    • Arguments

      public Arguments​(java.lang.String kripkeFilename, java.lang.String stateToCheckStr, FormulaInputSource formulaInputSource, java.lang.String modelInputStr, java.lang.Boolean runEndToEndTests, java.lang.Integer endToEndTestNum, java.lang.Boolean runOnlyMicrowave) throws java.io.IOException
      Constructor including state to check (the other constructor omits the state to check), the kripke file name,the model input source and the model input string.
      Parameters:
      kripkeFilename - String Filename of .txt file containing the kripke structure. Don't include the full path, just the filename. The file needs to be in the src/main/resources directory.
      stateToCheckStr - String name of the state to check, like "s0" or "s13". Constructor checks to ensure stateToCheckStr starts with lowercase "s" and next has an integer after that.
      formulaInputSource - Simple FormulaInputSource enum value that's either FILE or ARGUMENT. Refers to whether user specified the -f or -a flag. FILE means the model is supplied in a textfile specified after the -f flag in the command line arguments. ARGUMENT means the model itself is hardcoded in the command line argument after the -a flag.
      modelInputStr - String representing either the .txt filename where the model is supplied or is actual CTL model string itself. Whether this string is the filename or the model is determined by the above modelInputSource param - FILE means filename and ARGUMENT means the model itself.
      runEndToEndTests - specifying that the end to end tests should be run
      endToEndTestNum - specifying the end to end test number to run (optional)
      runOnlyMicrowave - specifying to only run the microwave example
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException
